Abstract¶

The purpose of this project is to visualize and analyze data through python. The selected data set is FIFA 19 complete player dataset (https://www.kaggle.com/karangadiya/fifa19), which contains 1826 data sets. The main tasks of this project are: Data Wrangling, EDA, Data Analysis.

The main modules used are: pandas, matplotlib, seaborn. After completing this project, the relationship between players'position and different features is obtained.

Introduction¶

FIFA 19 is a football simulation video game developed by EA Vancouver as part of Electronic Arts'FIFA series. It is a game developed on the basis of real players' information. Therefore, some basic information can be studied as real world data and some interesting conclusions can be found. In this project, I mainly studied the relationship between players'different positions and their wages, height, weight and clubs. After the study, we can have a more in-depth understanding of the football project, and at the same time, we can buy the right roles according to the conclusions in the game and set up better strategies.

Data Wrangling¶

In this part, I first delete the data containing zero and null values from the original file, and then select some features to start the research.

In [366]:
for row in range(len(data)):
    data.iloc[row,4] = re.sub('[€]','',data.iloc[row,4])
    if 'M' in data.iloc[row,4]:
        data.iloc[row,4] = float(re.sub('[M]','',data.iloc[row,4])) * 1000
    elif 'K' in data.iloc[row,4]:
        data.iloc[row,4] = float(re.sub('[K]','',data.iloc[row,4]))
data['Wage'] = data['Wage'].str.replace('[€K]','').astype(float)

In [371]:
def p_mean(ls):
    ft = 0
    amount = 0
    for each in ls:
        amount += q1.loc[each,'amount']
    for each in ls:
        ft += q1.loc[each,'Wage'] * q1.loc[each,'amount']
    return float(round(ft/amount,2))
In [377]:
Position = ['Forward','Midfielder','Back','GK']
pw = dict({'Wage':[p_mean(Forward),p_mean(Midfielder),p_mean(Back),p_mean(GK)]})
pw = pd.DataFrame(pw)
pw.index = Position
pw.plot(kind='bar')
plt.xticks(rotation=0, fontsize=15)
plt.ylabel('Wage')
plt.title('Average wages in four major positions of football',fontsize=20)
Out[377]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Average wages in four major positions of football')

According to the above, the average wages of the four positions of'Forward','Midfielder','Back','GK'are obtained. The relationship between them is' Forward' > 'Midfielder' > 'Back' > 'GK'.

In summary, forward and midfield have higher wages, and among them, 'RF','LF','LAM','RAM' pay is higher than other positions in the same profession. Through the two charts, we can also find that the lower the average wage is, which to some extent reflects that the current football strategy pays more attention to attack.

Conclusion¶

Throughout the project, I spent a lot of time on DATA WRANGLING. I think this is a very important step. Proper data wrangling will make data more intuitive and less error in EDA and Analysis. After studying the effects of different factors on players'positions, I found that Front-court players tend to get higher wages, and they have smaller size and more flexible operation. For teams with tactical bias to attack, the quality of Front-court players is relatively high.
